product_name: Anastasia Beverly HillsVelvety-Matte Precision Shaping Lip Liner
summary: SummaryHighlightsCruelty FreeVeganFull-pigment ABH lip pencil for seamless shaping, contouring and color payoff with extreme precision. Sculpt and define lips with the creamy (never shiny or slippery) formula or fill in lips with long-lasting, velvety-matte color that doesn’t feather. Customize your lip look with versatile shades.
details: DetailsBenefitsFull-pigment, precision lip pencil for shaping and contouring lipsWax-based formula delivers a seamless, matte finish that doesn't featherCreamy, smooth texture effortlessly glides without skipping or tuggingWood pencil allows you to sharpen to a fine tip for extreme-precision and crisp linesApplies quickly and easily with exact definition and comfortable wearabilitySquare shape doesn’t roll and is easy to grab in your beauty bagCan be worn all over the lip or paired with lipstick and glossVersatile, wide shade range of neutralsContains natural antioxidantsCan be worn alone or layeredDermatologist testedFree of: Parabens, Phthalates, Sulfate, Mineral Oil, Alcohol, Petrolatum, Lanolin-Derivate, PreservativesItem 2590199How To UseFirst, pull cap straight off when removing (don't twist). For extra precision, sharpen before each use. Line and sculpt the lips to create desired shape before applying lipstick. Use a shade that is slightly deeper than your lipstick for a fuller-looking effect.IngredientsC10-18 Triglycerides, Talc, Hydrogenated Vegetable Oil, Mica, Caprylic/Capric Triglyceride, Synthetic Japan Wax, Tocopherol, Ascorbyl Palmitate, Manganese Violet (CI 77742), Iron Oxides (CI 77491, CI 77499), Red 7 (CI 15850), Titanium Dioxide (CI 77891).Shipping & Coupon RestrictionsThis brand is excluded from most Ulta Beauty coupons.See brand eligibility details
how_to_use: First, pull cap straight off when removing (don't twist). For extra precision, sharpen before each use. Line and sculpt the lips to create desired shape before applying lipstick. Use a shade that is slightly deeper than your lipstick for a fuller-looking effect.

reviews.headline: Every other liner I try isn't as good as this one
reviews.comments:
So I was in store one day and tried nearly every brand of liner that had a tester, to find something truly cool toned that wouldn't pull orange or peach on me, as I'm very fair and very pink-toned, and it's a good thing I took a chance and swatched Raisin because it has become my every day, can't beat it liner. I have a purple undertone to my lips even though they're pale, and Raisin smudged out a bit is a perfect shade for me. Had I been searching online, wouldn't have guessed that. 
Buy the ABH sharpener for best results, I prefer these old school wooden pencils because they actually can sharpen to a fine point, and let's be real whatever plastic chemical is likely in the more modern liners should probably not be going on our mouths. It's a long pencil and will last ages, and they go on sale once or twice a year so they are a better value than the discount brands if you buy then.

faceoff_positive.comments: Hey there! I was able to try out this ABH Lip Liner recently and I'm actually quite impressed! Now I've gotta mention that I'm really visually impaired so it's difficult for me to apply Lip Liner properly. Now saying that, it's really easy to draw with. It draws perfect thin lines. It doesn't tug or skip. It usually only takes one pass to get the right Pigment. My favorite part is that it holds in place really well and keeps my Lipstick in place better. I can even use it as Lip color if I wanted to and just add a Gloss over it. It really helps make my lips look bigger and fuller. I can say that it pairs really well with ABH's Matte Lipstick. The color is super versatile but still elegant. I definitely recommend it!
faceoff_positive.headline: Super smooth!

faceoff_negative.comments: The reason this is not my favorite lip liner has nothing to do with the product itself, and therefore I hope the company is listening.  If you made this with one of those little sharpeners in the cap, it would have been a five-star.  If you had made the shape a cylinder rather than squared, it would have made a major difference.  The lip liner itself is fantastic: long-lasting, precise lining, not crumbly, just very creamy and smooth.  However, it wore down fairly.  It wouldn't fit in my regular sharpener and didn't come with one.  What a waste of a fantastic product.
faceoff_negative.headline: Beautiful and In need of Assistance
